"title": "5863: flattery",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5863",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Insincere and undeserved praise or words of encouragement, used with the intention of gaining favour with others.</p>\n<h2>Flattery is deceitful</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:2-Ps12:3\">PSA 12:2–12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:9\">PSA 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:20-Ps55:21\">PSA 55:20–55:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:4\">PSA 62:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:6\">PRO 27:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:8\">JER 9:8</a></p>\n<h2>The results of flattery are ruinous</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:28\">PRO 26:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:5\">PRO 29:5</a></p>\n<h2>Flattery is rejected by godly people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:21-Job32:22\">JOB 32:21–32:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:10\">GAL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:5-1Thess2:6\">1TH 2:5–2:6</a></p>\n<h2>Honesty is preferable to flattery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:23\">PRO 28:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:13\">PRO 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:9\">PRO 27:9</a></p>\n<h2>False teachers use flattery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17-Rom16:18\">ROM 16:17–16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3-2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:3–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:16-Jude1:19\">JUD 1:16–1:19</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of flattery</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:17-2Sam14:20\">2SA 14:17–14:20</a> <em>The woman from Tekoa flatters David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:2-2Sam15:6\">2SA 15:2–15:6</a> <em>Absalom to Israelites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:21\">DAN 6:21</a> <em>Daniel flatters the king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:16\">MAT 22:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14\">MRK 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:21\">LUK 20:21</a> <em>the Pharisees and Herodians to Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:21\">LUK 20:21</a> <em>The spies from the teachers of the law flatter Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:22\">ACT 12:22</a> <em>The crowds flatter Herod.</em></p>",
